Reasoning: The paper discusses a metric for network analysis and community detection, which are topics that fall under several CS sub-categories. The use of centrality measures and modularity-maximization methods suggest that cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Software Engineering) are likely sub-categories. The study of network structure and node rankings also suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as possible sub-categories. Finally, the use of a tunable parameter and comparison with alternative methods suggests cs.LG (Machine Learning) as a potential sub-category.
